body:
Should this lead to `flutter packages` commands, not `pub` commands?

1. Create new Flutter project
1. Open pubspec.yaml
1. Click the Get/Upgrade actions in the action strip

comment_data.body:
Good catch.  Behind the scenes we *are* calling the Flutter pub actions (by setting `FLUTTER_ROOT` as described here https://flutter.io/upgrading/) which is why those actions actually work but the labels might be confusing.  The tricky bit is that the labels are provided by the Dart plugin and we'd have to update them there.  That said, it'd be easy enough...  

Do you feel more specific labels would help here?

It's not just the labels -- it also seems to behave differently. If I create a new project (with File > Create), and the run `flutter packages get` in a terminal no changes are created in my local project dir, but if I click 'Get dendencies' in the action ribbon, then I get a `.pub` folder in my project dir.
Hmmmm.  Maybe @danrubel can speak to how `flutter packages get` is invoking `pub` but I think it's using the `--[no-]pub` option.  To be really consistent, we could do that too.

```
flutter packages get
```
invokes pub as ...
```
pub --verbosity=warning get --no-packages-dir --no-precompile
```

I don't think the dart plugin is calling `flutter packages get`, I think it's calling `pub get` with a special flutter env. var set. So we're getting the default value for the no packages flag (and flutter packages get passes in its own desired pref).

Mulling this over a bit, I'm OK with how we have it implemented but happy to explore refinements.

@mit-mit @devoncarew ?

sgtm. The default value for `--no-packages-dir` in pub will catch up with what flutter's doing today. But we may also want to expose these flutter specific options in a few places (a context menu, a top-level menu item). I'll create some issues for that.

Closing this in favor of #515 and #516.

Feel free to re-open if you feel they don't cover it.

Can you elaborate on how this is covered by #515 and #516? Those look like just adding more ways of invoking this, not a fix of what it's doing.

My core issue is that these actions behave differently from running `flutter packages` commands in a terminal. They should not.

Wishful thinking I guess. Especially in light of @devoncarew's comment:

> The default value for --no-packages-dir in pub will catch up with what flutter's doing today. 

The rub is that making the pub actions retargetable would require more coordination with the Dart plugin which I was hoping to avoid.  That said, if this is a nagging issue we can keep it open and I can work on a better solution.  I'm cool either way.
I'm generally worried about the UI not invoking what we expect from the terminal. Who knows how 'flutter packages' and 'pub' might diverge in the future...?
Ideal scenario: butterbar is not presented for pubspecs in flutter projects.  We present our own butterbar (same as for flutter.yaml?)
Closing as fixed by a host of changes, the last bit being tracked in #660.

milestone.title: On Deck

title: Pub vs flutter get
